<P></P>
<P><BR class=3Dclear></P>
<P><STRONG>About ISO <BR></STRONG>ISO is a global network of national =
standards=20
institutes from 157 countries. It has a current portfolio of more than =
17 000=20
standards for business, government and society. ISO's standards make up =
a=20
complete offering for all three dimensions of sustainable development =
=E2=80=93=20
economic, environmental and social. ISO standards provide solutions and =
achieve=20
benefits for almost all sectors of activity, including agriculture,=20
construction, mechanical engineering, manufacturing, distribution, =
transport,=20
medical devices, information and communication technologies, the =
environment,=20
energy, quality management, conformity assessment and services. </P>
<P></P>
<P><STRONG>About IEC<BR></STRONG>The IEC is the world's leading =
organization=20
that prepares and publishes International Standards for all electrical,=20
electronic and related technologies =E2=80=93 collectively known as =
"electrotechnology".=20
IEC Standards cover a vast range of technologies from power generation,=20
transmission and distribution to home appliances and office equipment,=20
semiconductors, fibre optics, batteries, solar energy, nanotechnology =
and marine=20
energy to mention just a few. Wherever you find electricity and =
electronics, you=20
find the IEC supporting safety and performance, the environment, =
electrical=20
energy efficiency and renewable energies. The IEC also manages =
conformity=20
assessment schemes that certify whether equipment, systems or components =
conform=20
to its International Standards.</P><BR><!--
